Nigerians To Watch Women’s Euro 2022, Copa America Finals On StarTimes Sadio Mane is set to make his competitive debut as a Bayern Munich player in today’s Supercup against RB Leipzig at 7:30 p.m. The match will be broadcast live and in HD by StarTimes, which has also launched W-sports, the first of its kind channel that provides live coverage of various women’s sports. 26 July 2022, Bavaria, Munich: Soccer: Bundesliga, training FC Bayern Munich before the Supercup at the training ground on S‰bener Straﬂe. Sadio Mane (l-r), Joshua Zirkzee and Leroy Sane of FC Bayern M¸nchen warm up. On Saturday (30.07.), FC Bayern will face RB Leipzig in the Supercup. Photo: Matthias Balk/dpa – IMPORTANT NOTE: In accordance with the requirements of the DFL Deutsche Fuﬂball Liga and the DFB Deutscher Fuﬂball-Bund, it is prohibited to use or have used photographs taken in the stadium and/or of the match in the form of sequence pictures and/or video-like photo series. (Photo by MATTHIAS BALK / DPA / dpa Picture-Alliance via AFP)  Tomorrow, the finals of Women’s Euro 2022 and Women’s Copa America will air on the W-Sports channel. Host nation, England, will take on Germany in the Euro final at Wembley Stadium by 5.00 p.m. England reached their first major tournament final since 2009 after they thrashed Sweden in the semifinals. Goals from Beth Mead, Lucy Bronze, Fran Kirby and Alessia Russo were enough to see off the Swedes in Sheffield. Their opponents, Germany, beat France 2-1, thanks to a brace from in-form striker – Alexandra Popp. The Germans will be looking to spoil the party tomorrow and clinch their remarkable ninth-ever Women’s EURO title. In South America, the final match of the Women’s Copa America, between Colombia and Brazil, will be played early Sunday morning at 1.00 a.m. Other women’s sports on the channel include motorsports, basketball, volleyball and cycling, among others. The channel is currently available to dish users (DTH) on StarTimes. 